"a.性急的，暴躁的 【英】 adj.性急的，暴躁的 (easily annoyed；irritable) 【考】 testy : annoy / tractable : control(易怒的容易被激怒/ 可驯服的容易被控制) 【记】 分割记忆：test(考试 )+y→为考试伤脑筋→ 不耐烦的 【例】 His voice turned testy.(他的语气变得 不耐烦了) adj. 性急的; 不耐烦的; 容易被激怒的 【记】test考试, y－总是考试－不耐烦的 【类】testy: annoy[offend] = tractable: control = hesitate: balk = pliable: influence易怒的容易被激怒[冒犯] = 可驯服的容易被控制 = 不情愿的容易被拒绝 = 顺从的容易被影响 【反】affable(adj 和蔼可亲的); open-minded(adj 虚心接受新思想的)『good humor/humorous』 【记】test + y 考试考得烦恼与暴躁，尤其是GRE testy (adj.)  early 15c., ""impetuous, rash,"" altered from Middle English testif ""headstrong"" (late 14c.), from Anglo-French testif, Old French testu (Modern French têtu) ""stubborn, headstrong, obstinate,"" literally ""heady,"" from teste ""head"" (see tete). Meaning ""easily irritated, irascible"" is first recorded 1520s. Related: Testily; testiness."
